            <title>[THRIFT-4328] Travis CI builds are timing out (job 1) and haxe builds are failing since 9/11</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-4328</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Need to split binary protocol cross tests to a new build job (previous combination of build jobs was too aggressive).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Need to fix haxe problem with builds that starts on 9/11.  Looks like a new version of hxcpp is to blame, and pinning to the previous one resolves it.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
